-- ================================================================
--  pfd.lua  --  Fused Flight Controller
--  ----------------------------------------------------------------
--  A single controller, holds ATTITUDE [pitch (x) + roll (z)] and ALTITUDE (y), and the four
--  rotor commands are the SUPERPOSITION of both:
--
--      motor = altitudeCollective  ±  pitchTrim  ±  rollTrim
--
--  Two independent control laws run every tick:
--
--    ALT  : physics-feed-forward + PI + vertical-velocity damping,
--           with an online lift-coefficient (k) estimator.  Holds a
--           commanded altitude against changing air pressure / mass.
--
--    STAB : two PID loops (pitch, roll) with derivative-on-angular-
--           velocity, keeping the airframe level.
--
--  Neither law is ever "off": both compute on every tick so every
--  graph stays live.  Superposition means the altitude solution sets
--  the hover power and the stabiliser only ever adds/removes a small
--  differential on top -- exactly how a physical quad behaves.
--
--  ----------------------------------------------------------------
--  
--  COMMANDS  (typed into the computer terminal)
--
--    pfd                primary flight display (default)
--    stab graph         stabiliser: motor flux + pitch/roll error
--    stab gains         stabiliser: kP/kI/kD contribution traces
--    alt  graph         altitude: collective RPM + altitude tracking
--    alt  gains         altitude: kP/kI/kD contribution traces
--
--    stab kp|ki|kd <n>  tune stabiliser gains
--    alt  kp|ki|kd <n>  tune altitude gains
--    alt  ff <n>        altitude fallback feed-forward constant
--    alt  set <n>       command a new target altitude
--    gr <n>             graph vertical half-range
--
--    save               persist all gains to disk
--    reset              clear every integrator
--    help               command list
--
--  [Redstone]  RIGHT side held briefly -> target altitude + step
--              LEFT  side held briefly -> target altitude - step
--
--  ----------------------------------------------------------------
--  QUICK TUNING
--
--  ATTITUDE
--    Barely reacts to tilt       -> raise stab kP
--    Oscillates side to side     -> lower stab kP   OR raise stab kD
--    Overshoots and bounces      -> raise stab kD
--    High-frequency jitter       -> lower stab kD
--    Settles slightly off-level  -> raise stab kI  (slowly)
--
--  ALTITUDE
--    Sinks/climbs at target      -> adjust alt ff
--    Slow to reach altitude      -> raise alt kP
--    Overshoots the level off    -> raise alt kD
--    Porpoises up and down       -> lower alt kP   OR raise alt kD
--    Settles a few blocks off    -> raise alt kI  (slowly)
-- ================================================================


